Implement `chipper ai` — generate AI instruction files for supported coding tools.

`chipper ai` (interactive):
  Prompt user to select which tools to generate files for.

`chipper ai --claude`:    writes CLAUDE.md
`chipper ai --cursor`:    writes .cursor/rules/chipper.mdc
`chipper ai --copilot`:   writes .github/copilot-instructions.md
`chipper ai --windsurf`:  writes .windsurfrules

Generated files should explain:
- The manifest format (chipper-slugs, chipper-queue)
- Available commands and their behavior
- Ticket states (todo, in_progress, done, cancelled, archived, unregistered, unsorted, orphaned)
- Slug and project identifier conventions
- How to interpret and act on ticket content in an AI session

Re-running chipper ai overwrites existing files with the current version.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding

